    "(2n = 16-32) and Pristimantis spp 51.",
    "(2n = 22-38), have experienced higher rates of karyotype change.",
    "On the other hand, other lineages, such as those leading to Leptobrachium ailaonicum, L. leishanense 14, and Rana temporaria 83, have had no detectable inter-chromosome exchange over the past 205 million years (Fig. 1).",
    "Nonetheless, this analysis of chromosome variation across the frog lineage is consistent with an overall slow rate of karyotype evolution 84.",
    "Considering rearrangement rate variation across taxa, we can ask whether any of the individual branches show an unusually high or low number of translocations relative to the overall pipanuran rate."
